Step 0 - 
cd ~/Linux-Lab-Assignment
mkdir Question4
cd Question4

pwd 

Step 1 - 
touch commands.txt output.txt explanation.txt
ls

Part 1 -
Commands - 
uptime

OUtput - 
12:53:37 up 5 days, 11:51, o users, load average: 7.49, 7.57, 5.81

Explanation - 
The uptime command displays how long the system has been running since the last boot.


Part 2 -
Commands - 
ps -u $USER

OUtput - 
PID TTY    TIME CMD
Explanation - 
ps -u $USER lists all processes running under the logged-in user account.


Part 3 -
Commands - 
top -u $USER

Explanation - 
The top -u $USER command displays real-time CPU usage of processes owned by the current user.
The process at the top of the list is consuming the highest CPU.


Part 4 -
Commands - 
sleep 300 &
jobs

OUtput - 
[1] 720 
Afters jobs
[1]+ Running       sleep 300 &

Explanation - 
sleep 300 & starts a command in the background.
The jobs command verifies that the background process is running.


Part 5 -
Commands - 
ps -o pid,ni,cmd -u $USER
renice 10 -p <PID>
ps -o pid,ni,cmd -p <PID>

OUtput - 
screenshot

Explanation - 
The renice command changes the priority of a running process.
A higher nice value means lower priority for the process.

Part 6 -
Commands - 
free -h

OUtput - 
screenshot 

Explanation - 
free -h shows total, used, and available memory in a human-readable format.

Part 7 -
Commands - 
df -h ~

OUtput - 
screenshot

Explanation - 
df -h ~ displays disk usage statistics of the filesystem containing the home directory.


Part 8 -
Commands - 
echo $SHELL

OUtput - 
/bin/bash

Explanation - 
This command displays the path of the shell currently in use.

Part 9 -
Commands - 
uname -a > system_report.txt

OUtput - 
Linux 7e385abb3de3 6.5.0-1024-aws #24-22.04.1-Ubuntu SMP Thu Jul 18 10:43:12 UTC 2024 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux

Explanation - 
This command redirects system information output into the system_report.txt file.


Part 10 -
Commands - 
ncdu ~

OUtput - 
bash: ncdu: command not found

Explanation - 
ncdu provides an interactive visualization of disk usage, showing directory sizes.
If the tool is not installed, the system displays an error message.








